Y.  Boston Streets Atlantic Ave Preceded by a flagman on foot, a modern diesel-electric locomotive proceeds along the two and one-half mile Union Freight Railroad tracks in Boston. Five General Electric diesel-electrics replaced ancient stea, engines on the once horse-powered line that connects Boston's North and South  stations.

DUE FOR DEMOLITIO In the path of the Boston Central Artery and to be razed in September are these buildings on the right side of  Atlantic av., looking south toward Dewey sq. More than 100 properties will be taken by the state south of Fort Hill sq. including those between 451 and 467 Atlantic av and others on Purchase Oliver, Pearl, Congress and Summer sts. MAR 11 1963 MAP SHOWING NEW ALFORD STREET BRIDGE connecting Charlestown and Everett which will be under construction sometime this spring. Present Alford Street Bridge is showed by heavy outline and will carry traffic as usual while shaded portico of new bridge (dotted lines) will be constructed first. State Public Works Commissioner Jack P. Ricciardi said bids will be opened March 12 and the structure will cost about $4,300,000. Boston Streets Alfort
